data.text: @sgcafan @transguysteve Sore arm. Have been warned by a few RA people I will likely get a flare, as my immune system will want to ramp up (normally we need to suppress it) & might find I get some more side effects in next 24/48 hrs as a result. But it’s all fine.
@Buddha_aka_me @transguysteve Good news, glad you were able to get your first dose!  No problems/discomfort I hope?

@PainsAnatomy ever seen, as they’re using it as a hub for our area of the county. They’ve done exceptionally well, plus needing to use the surgery outside of the vaccination days for regular patients!

@PainsAnatomy It’s a wait for too many for sure, but at least a start has been made & once vaccines are secured as needed, I imagine the biggest issue will be logistics & staffing levels needed to get it out there. Even our small GP surgery was packed with more volunteers, nurses etc than I’ve
@Buddha_aka_me Yeah I mean that’s a start, if I’m lucky I’ll get my first dose in November- December 🙄
@PainsAnatomy @transguysteve Not that it changes anything here until the 2nd dose, & Steven needs to get his (he’ll be called in with the 6th group). But glad I could at least get it done.
